events.name: Alabama Crimson Tide at Auburn Tigers

headlines.description: Trent Richardson rushed for a career-high 203 yards and AJ McCarron threw three first-half touchdown passes to lift No. 2 Alabama to a 42-14 victory over rival Auburn on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bama states its case, routs Auburn

events.name: Virginia Tech Hokies at Virginia Cavaliers

headlines.description: Logan Thomas threw for two touchdowns and ran for one and David Wilson scored on two long runs in the second half as Virginia Tech shut out Virginia 38-0 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Va. Tech into ACC title game

events.name: Notre Dame Fighting Irish at Stanford Cardinal

headlines.description: Stanford 28, Notre Dame 14
headlines.shortLinkText: Stanford's Luck passes Elway

events.name: Wyoming Cowboys at Boise State Broncos

headlines.description: Kellen Moore tossed three touchdown passes, including a 46-yarder on the final play of the first half, to lead No. 7 Boise State to a 36-14 victory over Wyoming on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Moore leads Boise's 2nd-half surge at Wyoming

events.name: Iowa State Cyclones at Oklahoma Sooners

headlines.description: Landry Jones threw for 256 yards, Blake Bell punched in two short touchdown runs and Oklahoma set up a Bedlam showdown for the Big 12 championship by beating Iowa State
headlines.shortLinkText: Sooners rip Iowa St. before Bedlam

events.name: Oregon State Beavers at Oregon Ducks

headlines.description: LaMichael James ran for 142 yards before leaving with what appeared to be a left elbow injury, and Oregon beat Oregon State 49-21 Saturday to clinch the Pac-12 North and a spot in the conference's first championship game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pac-12: Ducks in title game

events.name: Clemson Tigers at South Carolina Gamecocks

headlines.description: South Carolina 34, Clemson 13
headlines.shortLinkText: Shaw guides S. Carolina past sliding Clemson

events.name: Georgia Bulldogs at Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets

headlines.description: Aaron Murray threw four touchdown passes and No. 13 Georgia extended its domination over Georgia Tech, pulling away for a 31-17 victory Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray gets Georgia by Ga. Tech

events.name: Michigan State Spartans at Northwestern Wildcats

headlines.description: Keshawn Martin returned a punt 57 yards for a touchdown just before halftime and Kirk Cousins threw two TD passes to B.J. Cunningham as Michigan State warmed up for next week's Big Ten championship game by beating Northwestern 31-17 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Michigan St. whips Northwestern for 10th win

events.name: Ohio State Buckeyes at Michigan Wolverines

headlines.description: Denard Robinson accounted for five touchdowns, helping Michigan (No. 15 BCS, No. 17 AP) beat Ohio State 40-34 on Saturday and snap a school-record, seven-game losing streak in the rivalry.
headlines.shortLinkText: Michigan holds off Ohio State

events.name: Penn State Nittany Lions at Wisconsin Badgers

headlines.description: Montee Ball scored four more touchdowns in his pursuit of an NCAA record, powering Wisconsin to a 45-7 rout of Penn State and a spot in next week's Big Ten championship game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Badgers in Big Ten title game

events.name: Texas Tech Red Raiders at Baylor Bears

headlines.description: Nick Florence threw two long touchdown passes after Robert Griffin was knocked out of the game and Baylor extended its winning streak to four games with a 66-42 victory over Texas Tech on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Griffin hurt, but Baylor rolls

events.name: Rutgers Scarlet Knights at Connecticut Huskies

headlines.description: Running back Lyle McCombs and quarterback Scott McCummings each ran for two touchdowns as Connecticut upset Rutgers 40-22 on Saturday, ending the Scarlet Knights' hopes for a share of the Big East championship.
headlines.shortLinkText: UConn denies Rutgers share of Big East title

events.name: Cincinnati Bearcats at Syracuse Orange

headlines.description: Munchie Legaux threw for two touchdowns, one a short toss that turned into a backbreaking 69-yard score in the fourth quarter, and Tony Miliano kicked three field goals as Cincinnati beat Syracuse 30-13.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cincy keeps BCS hopes alive

events.name: Tennessee Volunteers at Kentucky Wildcats

headlines.description: CoShik Williams ran for a touchdown and senior wide receiver Matt Roark filled in at quarterback with 124 yards on 24 carries as Kentucky snapped a 26-game losing streak to Tennessee with a 10-7 victory on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kentucky ends 26-year hex vs. Vols

headlines.shortLinkText: W. Kentucky 41, Troy 18

events.name: Maryland Terrapins at NC State Wolfpack

headlines.description: Mike Glennon threw for a career-high five touchdowns, ran for another score and led North Carolina State's rally from 27 points down in the second half to beat Maryland 56-41 on Saturday
headlines.shortLinkText: NC State stuns Maryland with 35 points in fourth

events.name: Purdue Boilermakers at Indiana Hoosiers

headlines.description: Ralph Bolden scored one touchdown, Caleb TerBush threw for another and Carson Wiggs made three field goals Saturday to lead Purdue past Indiana 33-25 for the Old Oaken Bucket.
headlines.shortLinkText: Purdue tops Indiana to claim Old Oaken Bucket

events.name: Illinois Fighting Illini at Minnesota Golden Gophers

headlines.description: MarQueis Gray rushed for 167 yards and two touchdowns and threw for another score, guiding Minnesota past backsliding Illinois 27-7 on Saturday in the season finale and sending the Fighting Illini to their sixth straight defeat.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gray powers Minnesota past slumping Illinois

events.name: Duke Blue Devils at North Carolina Tar Heels

headlines.description: Dwight Jones had three touchdown catches while redshirt freshman Giovani Bernard ran for a season-high 165 yards and a score to help North Carolina beat Duke 37-21 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jones hauls in 3 TDs as Tar Heels defeat Duke

events.name: Vanderbilt Commodores at Wake Forest Demon Deacons

headlines.description: Zac Stacy ran for 184 yards and three touchdowns and Vanderbilt became bowl-eligible by beating sluggish Wake Forest 41-7 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vanderbilt bowl eligible after Wake Forest rout

headlines.shortLinkText: Marshall 34, East Carolina 27, OT

events.name: Missouri Tigers at Kansas Jayhawks

headlines.description: James Franklin rebounded from three early interceptions to toss two second-half touchdown passes, and Missouri rallied for a 24-10 victory over Kansas on Saturday in what could be the final edition of the 120-year-old Border War rivalry.
headlines.shortLinkText: Franklin shakes off early struggles, leads Mizzou

events.name: Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns at Arizona Wildcats

headlines.description: Nick Foles threw for 352 yards and three touchdowns in his final game for Arizona, and the Wildcats held off Louisiana-Lafayette 45-37 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Foles matches TD records as Arizona holds on

events.name: Washington State Cougars at Washington Huskies

headlines.description: Keith Price threw three touchdown passes to become Washington's all-time single-season leader in that category, the final one a 22-yard toss to Chris Polk, and Washington held off Washington State 38-21 on Saturdayto win the 104th Apple Cup.
headlines.shortLinkText: Price-led Washington tops Wazzou in Apple Cup
